	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=11758><span id= >chavr</span></a><br><span id=notbold>5 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I see alot of posts that people make saying an item should be able to go to all that are listed as using it.&nbsp;&nbsp;I agree in this only when everyone that benefits the most from the item has equal or better.  <br><br>This item benefits rangers,sk's and paladins more than any other class.  The combination of haste,int/wis,str and location mean that they can add some ac and some int/wis to a very nice haste item.  Hybrid classes have a hard time finding gear that will allow them to maximize ac and still broaden their mana pool.  <br><br>Yes all classes can be considered for this item, but if you have a paladin with an fbss and you give this to a wizard then something is wrong.  It is simply a matter of who benefits the most from it, and by giving stuff to those who can use it to maximum effectiveness you are thereby increasing the overall strength of your guild.</p>&nbsp;<br>Chavr Wyrmbane<br>65 Crusader<br>Druzzil Ro</td></td></tr>
