	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=2197&mid=99584845681169>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2197&mid=99584845681169>Haste vs. Caster Stats</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2197&mid=99584845681169#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jul 22nd 8:34 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=44631><span id=Sage>AzathothStrongbear</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>26 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.05]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You can get WIS, INT, and mana in a lot of different slots, a lot of different ways.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can have many items in may slots with WIS/INT/Mana and they will all add together.  However, you can only have 1 haste item contribute towards your overall haste.  For that reason, haste is more valuable than wisdom, int, or mana.  You can have two 6 wis ring to make up for not having this cloak.  You cannot have two 13% haste items to make up for the haste on this cloak, because two 13% haste items only give you 13% haste, not 26%.  That is why haste is always more important than any other stat on any item, and it is why haste items go to melees first.</p>&nbsp;<br>Azathoth Strongbear <br>60 Human Warrior<br>&lt;Shadowhunters&gt; E`Ci</td></td></tr>
